         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Monga ¶ 23/11/88. ¶ Most esteemed Baron. ¶  ¶ I have received your two letters ¶  with the enclosures and express my sincerest thanks for them. As I got a bad leg through a fall, I was unfortunately n...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.11.23</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Wilhelm Bäuerlen</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M21, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Darwinia%20taxifolia">Darwinia taxifolia</name>
                     </seg> (MEL 220083) from Clyde, NSW. MS is annotated by M: 'Darwinia virgata The petals are persistent, may therefore be calyx lobes. Bractiolae cymbiaem sed omnino obtusae!' [Bractioles hardened but all of them obtuse!]. M has also annotated the label: 'Darwinia virgata FvM var. with undeveloped setular calyx lobes'.</p>
               </note>Monga</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">23/11/88.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Geehrtester Herr Baron.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihre beiden Briefe mit Einlagen habe ich erhalten, u. sage Ihnen herzlichsten Dank dafür. Da ich durch einen Fall ein schlimmes Bein bekam konnte ich leider kürzlich nicht ausgehen, auch ist durch die Dürre u. Buschfeuer auch beinahe Alles abgebrannt, was die diesige Jahreszeit äusserst ungünstig für das Sammeln macht.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit den drei Ex. die ich jetzt sende, lege ich auch zwei verschiedene Arten von <name key="Darwinia%20taxifolia">Darwinia taxifolia</name> bei, damit Sie wenn Sie einmal Zeit haben dieselben genauerer Vergleichung unterwerfen können. Doch so ziemlich in derselben Lokalität u. auf derselben geol. Formation vorkommend sind die Pflanzen </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">im</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Wuchs</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> sehr verschieden. Während die grosse rothblumige Art immer beinahe ganz flach am Boden liegt, ist die andre Art immer ganz aufrecht. Frucht konnte ich jetzt noch nicht finden.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Was Ihre Fragen betrifft, so scheinen die Blumen von <name key="Haloragis%20monosperma">Haloragis monosperma</name> keinen Geruch zu haben. […]</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sheet cut off, an unknown amount of text missing with only the tops of some letters on the next line remaining.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nach der Frucht von Eriostomen phyllicioides will ich mich bei der ersten Gelegenheit umsehen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit besten Wünschen für Ihre Gesundheit verbleibe ich Ihnen stets ergeben</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Wilhelm Bäuerlen</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>c/o Mr George MacRae</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Clyde Road</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Braidwood</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>— N.S.W. —</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Monga<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">NSW.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">23/11/88.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Most esteemed Baron.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have received your two letters<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letters not found.</p>
               </note> with the enclosures and express my sincerest thanks for them. As I got a bad leg through a fall, I was unfortunately not able to go out lately. Besides, because of the drought and the bushfires nearly everything is burnt, which makes the present season very unfavourable for collecting.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With the three specimens I am sending now I also enclose two different kinds of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Darwinia%20taxifolia">Darwinia taxifolia</name>
               </seg> so that, when you have some time, you can subject them to a more detailed comparison. Although they occur in much the same locality and on the same geological formation, the plants are very different <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">in their habit</hi>
               </seg>. While the large red-flowering kind always lies almost flat on the ground, the other one is completely erect. I could not yet find any fruit.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In regard to your question, the flowers of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Haloragis%20monosperma">Haloragis monosperma</name>
               </seg> do not seem to have any odour. […]<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sheet cut off; see n. 2 above.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will look for fruit of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Eriostemon%20phyllicioides">Eriostemon phyllicioides</name>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eriostemon phylicioides</seg>?</p>
               </note> at the first opportunity.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With best wishes for your health, I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">your always devoted</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wilhelm Bäuerlen</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>c/o Mr George McRae</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Clyde Road</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Braidwood</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>— N.S.W. —</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Darwinia%20taxifolia">Darwinia taxifolia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eriostemon%20phyllicioides">Eriostemon phyllicioides</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Haloragis%20monosperma">Haloragis monosperma</name>
            </p>
